DiagramMarkdown <p>Below you should see diagram Page-1: </p> <pre><code>![Page-1](test.drawio)
</code></pre> DiagramMarkdown <p>Below you should see diagram Page-2: </p> <pre><code>![Page-2](test.drawio)
</code></pre> DiagramMarkdown <p>Below you should see the diagram Page-2 using the page attribute: </p> <pre><code>![Some alt text](test.drawio){ page="Page-2" }
</code></pre> DiagramMarkdown <p>If the alt text doesn't exist as a page it will fallback to the first page of your diagram. Below you should therefore see Page-1 (default): </p> <p>Furthoremore, you should see a warning in your mkdocs server similar to:</p> <pre><code>WARNING -  Warning: Found 0 results for page name 'Page-3' for diagram 'test.drawio' on path '/tmp/mkdocs_ce1qjhyn/test2'
</code></pre> <pre><code>![Page-3](test.drawio)
</code></pre> DiagramMarkdown <p>If the alt text and page attribute don't exist as a page, it will fallback to the first page of your diagram. Below you should therefore see Page-1 (default): </p> <p>Furthoremore, you should see a warning in your mkdocs server similar to:</p> <pre><code>WARNING -  Warning: Found 0 results for page name 'Page-3' for diagram 'test.drawio' on path '/tmp/mkdocs_ce1qjhyn/test2'
</code></pre> <pre><code>![Some alt text](test.drawio){ page="Page-3" }
</code></pre> DiagramMarkdown <p>Pagging logic for SVG diagrams is skip as only a single page can be exported as an SVG drawio diagram.</p> <p></p> <pre><code>![Some alt text](test.drawio.svg){ page="Page-3" }
</code></pre>
